HEADWORD: Tomfoolery
<hw>Tom`fool"er*y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Trifling or
silly behavior done mostly for amusement; foolishness; fooling
around.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> tomfoolishness.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

